  "text": "There is evidence that MDRs can also function as peptide transporters: for example, mouse MDR3, when expressed in yeast, can transport a-factor at a low efficiency [CITATION_1] , and there is evidence that MDR1 can transport many hydrophobic peptides [CITATION_2] .",
